Source:
http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/view/development/chapter06/binutils.html

Download binutils source for your particular Ubuntu version from https://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/binutils/
(check binutils version using "ld -v" command.) 

Build:

Inside the binutils main directory:
mkdir -v build
cd       build

../configure --prefix=/usr/cdi       \
             --enable-ld=default \
             --enable-plugins    \
             --enable-shared     \
             --disable-werror    \
             --with-system-zlib
make tooldir=/usr/cdi
make tooldir=/usr/cdi install

If the build is succesful the binaries of the custom binutils can be found in /usr/cdi/bin directory.
